qTextArr: ["You can't think how glad I am to see you again, you dear old thing!"]
qText: You can't think how glad I am to see you again, you dear old thing!
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr:
["When _I'm_ a Duchess,", "I won't have any pepper in my kitchen _at all_. Soup
does very well without--Maybe it's always pepper that makes people
hot-tempered,", "and vinegar that makes them sour--and camomile that makes
them bitter--and--and barley-sugar and such things that make children
sweet-tempered. I only wish people knew _that_: then they wouldn't be
so stingy about it, you know--"]
qText:
When _I'm_ a Duchess, I won't have any pepper in my kitchen _at all_. Soup
does very well without--Maybe it's always pepper that makes people
hot-tempered, and vinegar that makes them sour--and camomile that makes
them bitter--and--and barley-sugar and such things that make children
sweet-tempered. I only wish people knew _that_: then they wouldn't be
so stingy about it, you know--
speaker: Alice

qTextArr:
["You're thinking
about something, my dear, and that makes you forget to talk. I can't
tell you just now what the moral of that is, but I shall remember it in
a bit."]
qText:
You're thinking
about something, my dear, and that makes you forget to talk. I can't
tell you just now what the moral of that is, but I shall remember it in
a bit.
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["Perhaps it hasn't one,"]
qText: Perhaps it hasn't one,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Tut, tut, child!', "Everything's got a moral, if only\nyou can find it."]
qText:
Tut, tut, child! Everything's got a moral, if only
you can find it.
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["The game's going on rather better now,"]
qText: The game's going on rather better now,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["'Tis so,", "and the moral of that is--'Oh, 'tis love,\n'tis love, that makes the world go round!'"]
qText:
'Tis so, and the moral of that is--'Oh, 'tis love,
'tis love, that makes the world go round!'
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['Somebody said,', "that it's done by everybody minding\ntheir own business!"]
qText:
Somebody said, that it's done by everybody minding
their own business!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Ah, well! It means much the same thing,', "and the moral of\n_that_ is--'Take care of the sense, and the sounds will take care of\nthemselves.'"]
qText:
Ah, well! It means much the same thing, and the moral of
_that_ is--'Take care of the sense, and the sounds will take care of
themselves.'
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['How fond she is of finding morals in things!']
qText: How fond she is of finding morals in things!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["I dare say you're wondering why I don't put my arm round your waist,", "the reason is, that I'm doubtful about\nthe temper of your flamingo. Shall I try the experiment?"]
qText:
I dare say you're wondering why I don't put my arm round your waist, the reason is, that I'm doubtful about
the temper of your flamingo. Shall I try the experiment?
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['He might bite,']
qText: He might bite,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Very true,', "flamingoes and mustard both bite. And\nthe moral of that is--'Birds of a feather flock together.'"]
qText:
Very true, flamingoes and mustard both bite. And
the moral of that is--'Birds of a feather flock together.'
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["Only mustard isn't a bird,"]
qText: Only mustard isn't a bird,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Right, as usual,', 'what a clear way you have of\nputting things!']
qText:
Right, as usual, what a clear way you have of
putting things!
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["It's a mineral, I _think_,"]
qText: It's a mineral, I _think_,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Of course it is,', "there's a large mustard-mine near here.\nAnd the moral of that is--'The more there is of mine, the less there is\nof yours.'"]
qText:
Of course it is, there's a large mustard-mine near here.
And the moral of that is--'The more there is of mine, the less there is
of yours.'
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['Oh, I know!', "it's a vegetable. It doesn't look like one, but it is."]
qText: Oh, I know! it's a vegetable. It doesn't look like one, but it is.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr:
['I quite agree with you,', "and the moral of that
is--'Be what you would seem to be'--or if you'd like it put more
simply--'Never imagine yourself not to be otherwise than what it might
appear to others that what you were or might have been was not
otherwise than what you had been would have appeared to them to be
otherwise.'"]
qText:
I quite agree with you, and the moral of that
is--'Be what you would seem to be'--or if you'd like it put more
simply--'Never imagine yourself not to be otherwise than what it might
appear to others that what you were or might have been was not
otherwise than what you had been would have appeared to them to be
otherwise.'
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['I think I should understand that better,', "if I had it written down: but I can't quite follow it as you say it."]
qText: I think I should understand that better, if I had it written down: but I can't quite follow it as you say it.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["That's nothing to what I could say if I chose,"]
qText: That's nothing to what I could say if I chose,
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["Pray don't trouble yourself to say it any longer than that,"]
qText: Pray don't trouble yourself to say it any longer than that,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["Oh, don't talk about trouble!", "I make you a present\nof everything I've said as yet."]
qText:
Oh, don't talk about trouble! I make you a present
of everything I've said as yet.
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['A cheap sort of present!', "I'm glad they don't give\nbirthday presents like that!"]
qText:
A cheap sort of present! I'm glad they don't give
birthday presents like that!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Thinking again?']
qText: Thinking again?
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ["I've a right to think,"]
qText: I've a right to think,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Just about as much right,', 'as pigs have to fly; and\nthe m--']
qText:
Just about as much right, as pigs have to fly; and
the m--
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['A fine day, your Majesty!']
qText: A fine day, your Majesty!
speaker: The Duchess

qTextArr: ['Now, I give you fair warning,', 'either you or your head must be off, and that in\nabout half no time! Take your choice!']
qText:
Now, I give you fair warning, either you or your head must be off, and that in
about half no time! Take your choice!
speaker: The Queen

qTextArr: ["Let's go on with the game,"]
qText: Let's go on with the game,
speaker: The Queen

qTextArr: ['Off with his head!', 'Off with\nher head!']
qText:
Off with his head! Off with
her head!
speaker: The Queen
refExp: the Queen never left off quarrelling with the other players and shouting

qTextArr: ['Have\nyou seen the Mock Turtle yet?']
qText:
Have
you seen the Mock Turtle yet?
speaker: The Queen
refExp: the Queen left off quite out of breath and said to Alice

qTextArr: ['No,', "I don't even know what a Mock Turtle is."]
qText: No, I don't even know what a Mock Turtle is.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["It's the thing Mock Turtle Soup is made from,"]
qText: It's the thing Mock Turtle Soup is made from,
speaker: The Queen

qTextArr: ['I never saw one, or heard of one,']
qText: I never saw one, or heard of one,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Come on, then,', 'and he shall tell you his history,']
qText: Come on, then, and he shall tell you his history,
speaker: The Queen

qTextArr: ['You are all pardoned.']
qText: You are all pardoned.
speaker: The King Of Hearts
refExp: the King say in a low voice to the company

qTextArr: ["Come, _that's_ a\ngood thing!"]
qText:
Come, _that's_ a
good thing!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr:
['Up, lazy
thing!', 'and take this young lady to see the Mock
Turtle, and to hear his history. I must go back and see after some
executions I have ordered;']
qText:
Up, lazy
thing! and take this young lady to see the Mock
Turtle, and to hear his history. I must go back and see after some
executions I have ordered;
speaker: The Queen

qTextArr: ['What fun!']
qText: What fun!
speaker: The Gryphon
refExp: said the Gryphon half to itself half to Alice

qTextArr: ['What _is_ the fun?']
qText: What _is_ the fun?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Why, _she_,', "It's all her fancy, that: they never\nexecutes nobody, you know. Come on!"]
qText:
Why, _she_, It's all her fancy, that: they never
executes nobody, you know. Come on!
speaker: The Gryphon
menEnts: [[['The Queen']], [['The Queen'], ['The Queen', 'The King Of Hearts', 'The Executioner'], ['Alice']]]

qTextArr: ["Everybody says 'come on!' here,", 'I never was so ordered about in all my life, never!']
qText: Everybody says 'come on!' here, I never was so ordered about in all my life, never!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['What is his sorrow?']
qText: What is his sorrow?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["It's all\nhis fancy, that: he hasn't got no sorrow, you know. Come on!"]
qText:
It's all
his fancy, that: he hasn't got no sorrow, you know. Come on!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['This here young lady,', 'she wants for to know your\nhistory, she do.']
qText:
This here young lady, she wants for to know your
history, she do.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["I'll tell it her,", "sit\ndown, both of you, and don't speak a word till I've finished."]
qText:
I'll tell it her, sit
down, both of you, and don't speak a word till I've finished.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["I don't see how he can _ever_ finish, if he doesn't begin."]
qText: I don't see how he can _ever_ finish, if he doesn't begin.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Once,', 'I was a real\nTurtle.']
qText:
Once, I was a real
Turtle.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Hjckrrh!']
qText: Hjckrrh!
speaker: The Gryphon
refExp: broken only by an occasional exclamation of Hjckrrh from the Gryphon

qTextArr: ['When we were little,', 'we went to school in the\nsea. The master was an old Turtle--we used to call him Tortoise--']
qText:
When we were little, we went to school in the
sea. The master was an old Turtle--we used to call him Tortoise--
speaker: The Mock Turtle
menEnts: [[['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle']], [['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['Tortoise'], ['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['Tortoise'], ['Tortoise']]]

qTextArr: ["Why did you call him Tortoise, if he wasn't one?"]
qText: Why did you call him Tortoise, if he wasn't one?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['We called him Tortoise because he taught us,', 'really you are very dull!']
qText: We called him Tortoise because he taught us, really you are very dull!
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['You ought to be ashamed of yourself for asking such a simple\nquestion,']
qText:
You ought to be ashamed of yourself for asking such a simple
question,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["Drive on, old fellow! Don't be all\nday about it!"]
qText:
Drive on, old fellow! Don't be all
day about it!
speaker: The Gryphon
refExp: the Gryphon said to the Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["Yes, we went to school in the sea, though you mayn't believe it--"]
qText: Yes, we went to school in the sea, though you mayn't believe it--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["I never said I didn't!"]
qText: I never said I didn't!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['You did,']
qText: You did,
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Hold your tongue!']
qText: Hold your tongue!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['We had the best of educations--in fact, we went to school every day--']
qText: We had the best of educations--in fact, we went to school every day--
speaker: The Mock Turtle
menEnts: [[['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle'], ['The Gryphon', 'The Mock Turtle']]]

qTextArr: ["_I've_ been to a day-school, too,", "you needn't be so\nproud as all that."]
qText:
_I've_ been to a day-school, too, you needn't be so
proud as all that.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['With extras?']
qText: With extras?
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Yes,', 'we learned French and music.']
qText: Yes, we learned French and music.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['And washing?']
qText: And washing?
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Certainly not!']
qText: Certainly not!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["Ah! then yours wasn't a really good school,", "Now at _ours_ they had at the end of the bill,\n'French, music, _and washing_--extra.'"]
qText:
Ah! then yours wasn't a really good school, Now at _ours_ they had at the end of the bill,
'French, music, _and washing_--extra.'
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["You couldn't have wanted it much,", 'living at the bottom\nof the sea.']
qText:
You couldn't have wanted it much, living at the bottom
of the sea.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["I couldn't afford to learn it.", 'I\nonly took the regular course.']
qText:
I couldn't afford to learn it. I
only took the regular course.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['What was that?']
qText: What was that?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Reeling and Writhing, of course, to begin with,', 'and then the different branches of Arithmetic--Ambition,\nDistraction, Uglification, and Derision.']
qText:
Reeling and Writhing, of course, to begin with, and then the different branches of Arithmetic--Ambition,
Distraction, Uglification, and Derision.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["I never heard of 'Uglification,'", 'What is it?']
qText: I never heard of 'Uglification,' What is it?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['What! Never heard of\nuglifying!', 'You know what to beautify is, I suppose?']
qText:
What! Never heard of
uglifying! You know what to beautify is, I suppose?
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Yes,', 'it means--to--make--anything--prettier.']
qText: Yes, it means--to--make--anything--prettier.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Well, then,', "if you don't know what to uglify\nis, you _are_ a simpleton."]
qText:
Well, then, if you don't know what to uglify
is, you _are_ a simpleton.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['What else had you to learn?']
qText: What else had you to learn?
speaker: Alice
refExp: she turned to the Mock Turtle and said

qTextArr:
['Well, there was Mystery,', '--Mystery, ancient and modern, with
Seaography: then Drawling--the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,
that used to come once a week: _he_ taught us Drawling, Stretching, and
Fainting in Coils.']
qText:
Well, there was Mystery, --Mystery, ancient and modern, with
Seaography: then Drawling--the Drawling-master was an old conger-eel,
that used to come once a week: _he_ taught us Drawling, Stretching, and
Fainting in Coils.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['What was _that_ like?']
qText: What was _that_ like?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["Well, I can't show it you myself,", "I'm too\nstiff. And the Gryphon never learnt it."]
qText:
Well, I can't show it you myself, I'm too
stiff. And the Gryphon never learnt it.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["Hadn't time,", 'I went to the Classics master,\nthough. He was an old crab, _he_ was.']
qText:
Hadn't time, I went to the Classics master,
though. He was an old crab, _he_ was.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['I never went to him,', 'he taught\nLaughing and Grief, they used to say.']
qText:
I never went to him, he taught
Laughing and Grief, they used to say.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['So he did, so he did,']
qText: So he did, so he did,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['And how many hours a day did you do lessons?']
qText: And how many hours a day did you do lessons?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Ten hours the first day,', 'nine the next, and so\non.']
qText:
Ten hours the first day, nine the next, and so
on.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['What a curious plan!']
qText: What a curious plan!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["That's the reason they're called lessons,", 'because they lessen from day to day.']
qText: That's the reason they're called lessons, because they lessen from day to day.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Then the eleventh day must have been\na holiday?']
qText:
Then the eleventh day must have been
a holiday?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Of course it was,']
qText: Of course it was,
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['And how did you manage on the twelfth?']
qText: And how did you manage on the twelfth?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["That's enough about lessons,", 'tell her something about the games now.']
qText: That's enough about lessons, tell her something about the games now.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Same as if he had a bone in his throat,']
qText: Same as if he had a bone in his throat,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['You may not have lived much under the sea--']
qText: You may not have lived much under the sea--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["I haven't,"]
qText: I haven't,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['and perhaps you were never even introduced to a lobster--']
qText: and perhaps you were never even introduced to a lobster--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['I once tasted--']
qText: I once tasted--
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['No, never']
qText: No, never
speaker: Alice
refExp: Alice began to say I once tasted but checked herself hastily and said

qTextArr: ['--so you can have no idea what a delightful thing a\nLobster Quadrille is!']
qText:
--so you can have no idea what a delightful thing a
Lobster Quadrille is!
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['No, indeed,', 'What sort of a dance is it?']
qText: No, indeed, What sort of a dance is it?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Why,', 'you first form into a line along the\nsea-shore--']
qText:
Why, you first form into a line along the
sea-shore--
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Two lines!', "Seals, turtles, salmon, and so on;\nthen, when you've cleared all the jelly-fish out of the way--"]
qText:
Two lines! Seals, turtles, salmon, and so on;
then, when you've cleared all the jelly-fish out of the way--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['_That_ generally takes some time,']
qText: _That_ generally takes some time,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['--you advance twice--']
qText: --you advance twice--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Each with a lobster as a partner!']
qText: Each with a lobster as a partner!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Of course,', 'advance twice, set to partners--']
qText: Of course, advance twice, set to partners--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['--change lobsters, and retire in same order,']
qText: --change lobsters, and retire in same order,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Then, you know,', 'you throw the--']
qText: Then, you know, you throw the--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['The lobsters!']
qText: The lobsters!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['--as far out to sea as you can--']
qText: --as far out to sea as you can--
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Swim after them!']
qText: Swim after them!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Turn a somersault in the sea!']
qText: Turn a somersault in the sea!
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Change lobsters again!']
qText: Change lobsters again!
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["Back to land again, and that's all the first figure,"]
qText: Back to land again, and that's all the first figure,
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['It must be a very pretty dance,']
qText: It must be a very pretty dance,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Would you like to see a little of it?']
qText: Would you like to see a little of it?
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Very much indeed,']
qText: Very much indeed,
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["Come, let's try the first figure!", 'We can do without lobsters, you know. Which shall sing?']
qText: Come, let's try the first figure! We can do without lobsters, you know. Which shall sing?
speaker: The Mock Turtle
refExp: said the Mock Turtle to the Gryphon
menEnts: [[['The Mock Turtle', 'The Gryphon']], [['The Mock Turtle', 'The Gryphon'], ['The Gryphon']]]

qTextArr: ['Oh, _you_ sing,', "I've forgotten the words."]
qText: Oh, _you_ sing, I've forgotten the words.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["Thank you, it's a very interesting dance to watch,", 'and I do so like that\ncurious song about the whiting!']
qText:
Thank you, it's a very interesting dance to watch, and I do so like that
curious song about the whiting!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Oh, as to the whiting,', "they--you've seen them,\nof course?"]
qText:
Oh, as to the whiting, they--you've seen them,
of course?
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Yes,', "I've often seen them at dinn--"]
qText: Yes, I've often seen them at dinn--
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["I don't know where Dinn may be,", "but if you've\nseen them so often, of course you know what they're like."]
qText:
I don't know where Dinn may be, but if you've
seen them so often, of course you know what they're like.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['I believe so,', "They have their tails in\ntheir mouths--and they're all over crumbs."]
qText:
I believe so, They have their tails in
their mouths--and they're all over crumbs.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ["You're wrong about the crumbs,", 'crumbs would\nall wash off in the sea. But they _have_ their tails in their mouths;\nand the reason is--']
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ['Tell her about the reason and all that,']
qText: Tell her about the reason and all that,
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr:
['The reason is,', "that they _would_ go with the
lobsters to the dance. So they got thrown out to sea. So they had to
fall a long way. So they got their tails fast in their mouths. So they
couldn't get them out again. That's all."]
qText:
The reason is, that they _would_ go with the
lobsters to the dance. So they got thrown out to sea. So they had to
fall a long way. So they got their tails fast in their mouths. So they
couldn't get them out again. That's all.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Thank you,', "it's very interesting. I never knew so much\nabout a whiting before."]
qText:
Thank you, it's very interesting. I never knew so much
about a whiting before.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['I can tell you more than that, if you like,', "Do you\nknow why it's called a whiting?"]
qText:
I can tell you more than that, if you like, Do you
know why it's called a whiting?
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['I never thought about it,', 'Why?']
qText: I never thought about it, Why?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['_It does the boots and shoes_,']
qText: _It does the boots and shoes_,
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['Does the boots and shoes!']
qText: Does the boots and shoes!
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Why, what are _your_ shoes done with?', 'I mean, what\nmakes them so shiny?']
qText:
Why, what are _your_ shoes done with? I mean, what
makes them so shiny?
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["They're done with blacking, I believe."]
qText: They're done with blacking, I believe.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Boots and shoes under the sea,', 'are done with a whiting. Now you know.']
qText: Boots and shoes under the sea, are done with a whiting. Now you know.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['And what are they made of?']
qText: And what are they made of?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Soles and eels, of course,', 'any shrimp could have told you that.']
qText: Soles and eels, of course, any shrimp could have told you that.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ["If I'd been the whiting,", "I'd have said to the porpoise, 'Keep back,\nplease: we don't want _you_ with us!'"]
qText:
If I'd been the whiting, I'd have said to the porpoise, 'Keep back,
please: we don't want _you_ with us!'
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['They were obliged to have him with them,', 'no\nwise fish would go anywhere without a porpoise.']
qText:
They were obliged to have him with them, no
wise fish would go anywhere without a porpoise.
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["Wouldn't it really?"]
qText: Wouldn't it really?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Of course not,', "why, if a fish came to _me_,\nand told me he was going a journey, I should say 'With what porpoise?'"]
qText:
Of course not, why, if a fish came to _me_,
and told me he was going a journey, I should say 'With what porpoise?'
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["Don't you mean 'purpose'?"]
qText: Don't you mean 'purpose'?
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['I mean what I say,']
qText: I mean what I say,
speaker: The Mock Turtle

qTextArr: ["Come, let's hear some of _your_ adventures."]
qText: Come, let's hear some of _your_ adventures.
speaker: The Gryphon

qTextArr: ['I could tell you my adventures--beginning from this morning,', "but it's no use going back to yesterday,\nbecause I was a different person then."]
qText:
I could tell you my adventures--beginning from this morning, but it's no use going back to yesterday,
because I was a different person then.
speaker: Alice

qTextArr: ['Explain all that,']
